I recommend using the spreadsheet with Excel. In case you can't or don't want to, there is a link to the Google Sheets version below.
Google Sheets runs somewhat slower, and this version may not be updated as frequently as the Excel version.
Due to a few differences between the programs, the Google Sheets version might not work as well as the other one. Last time I checked it
appeared functional.

WH40k Point Efficiency Calculator v3.2a for Google Sheets:
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1MulY2XkRvbDQdlCib8-FSxtTQx221CbhKTlfiOlHx0w/edit#gid=634049933

Click File -> Make a copy to use it
